  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Enterprise-Grade Infrastructure That Grows With Your Business
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Cloud-based infrastructure provides reliable, scalable platform for
            scheduling operations without server management overhead. CalendHub
            runs on AWS infrastructure with 99.9% uptime guarantee backed by
            service level agreement. Multiple availability zones ensure
            redundancy - if one data center experiences issues, traffic
            automatically routes to healthy infrastructure without service
            interruption. This architecture delivers enterprise reliability for
            organizations where calendar downtime means missed meetings, lost
            revenue, and damaged customer relationships.
          </p>

          <p>
            Automatic scaling handles usage fluctuations seamlessly. When
            booking volume spikes during business hours or campaign launches,
            infrastructure scales computing resources to maintain performance.
            When demand decreases, resources scale down to optimize costs. This
            elasticity ensures consistently fast response times regardless of
            concurrent users or booking activity. Teams never experience
            slowdowns during peak usage periods, and organizations avoid paying
            for unused capacity during quieter times.
          </p>

          <p>
            Global content delivery network accelerates calendar loading for
            users worldwide. Static assets and calendar data cache at edge
            locations closest to users, reducing latency significantly. Someone
            accessing scheduling pages from Tokyo experiences the same
            responsive performance as someone in New York. This geographic
            distribution becomes critical for international teams and businesses
            serving global customer bases where slow page loads directly impact
            booking conversion rates and user satisfaction.
          </p>

          <p>
            Automated backups and disaster recovery protect calendar data
            without manual intervention. Multiple daily backups with
            point-in-time recovery capability mean data remains safe even in
            catastrophic scenarios. If accidental deletion or data corruption
            occurs, administrators can restore calendars to any point within
            retention period. This protection operates continuously in
            background - no backup schedules to configure, no storage limits to
            monitor, no recovery procedures to test manually. Cloud
            infrastructure handles all data protection automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

