              CalendHub infrastructure runs on Amazon Web Services, leveraging
              proven cloud platform used by millions of applications worldwide.
              Multi-region architecture with automated failover ensures service
              continuity even during data center outages. Load balancers
              distribute traffic across multiple application servers,
              eliminating single points of failure. Database replication
              provides redundant data storage with automatic promotion if
              primary database becomes unavailable. CloudFront CDN caches assets
              globally for fast loading regardless of user location. Security
              monitoring operates 24/7 with automated threat detection and
              response. This enterprise architecture delivers reliability
              previously available only to organizations with dedicated
              infrastructure teams, now accessible through simple SaaS
              subscription without technical expertise required.
